Why casts: unified syntax (see lexical_cast), easier to grep, ugly (reason to avoid)
static_cast: typically (don't) use this
const_cast: operator[]const or similar (but do not modify consts), C interfaces

RTTI: polymorphic classes only (at least one virtual function).
typeid/type_info (opaque)
dynamic_cast: use virtual functions; example: split array into several

explicit constructor
mutable field: mutex

